This is not worth discussing cause you are beating a dead horse.. Verant said Manaburn is balanced end of story but I will fancy your post.<br>
<br>
Scenario 1.<br>
<br>
Will rarely happen... Almost all of the wizards on this server are good natured.. No one would knowingly do that.. And if they did.. It would be here the next day.. Thats stealing in my book.<br>
<br>
Scenario 2.<br>
<br>
If the other group gets there first, they got it.. Wizards will check for kunark dragon pops but won't stawl the zones looking for them.  There is plenty of time to form up a raid.  Most wizards with manaburn have raids to do and won't leave them for a Kunark dragon.<br>
<br>
Scenario 3.<br>
<br>
Wizards aren't useless OOM... I can use click nukes or mana robe or med up and get my mana back up fast. I use manaburn as a tacticular nuke in 100+ hp mobs.. People arent gonna be zerging things with wizards.. The novelty will wear off and people will want a challenge or they would already bring 20 normal nuking wizards or rogues or even warriors.<br>
<br>
Comparisons<br>
<br>
Um Dire charm owns all AA. You see logs of a dire charm giant against AoW? <br>
<br>
Solutions<br>
<br>
Making it 30 person more resistable won't do jack cause then you would just bring an extra 2 wizards to compensate.. Well it would piss people off thats all it would do.  Don't think you can make a spell not work against a group of unrelated mobs like that unless you nerf it for all under 32k mobs.  Verant most likely won't change manaburn cause most people don't care.. Why do you care so much? You a voice for the smaller guilds? or just want another RBB?<br>
<br>
AOE<br>
<br>
Why was AE brought up? anyway  I perfer quading for faster exp but AE if the good is really good can beat quading and by no means is AE totally safe.. in an average AE group the exp isnt that much better than a half decent normal group.. its just more fun in my opinion.<br>
<br>
<br>
You forgot to mention the benefits as people who would never have a chance at an epic cause their guild is too small can get a team of manaburn wizards to do the dirty work for them and get their chance at their epic drop.<br>
<br>
There have been reports of 1 groups of melee taking out kunark dragons.. is that fair too?<br>
<br>
It all boils down to who arrives first.. Doesn't matter the way you kill it.. Everyone has a fair chance that way. <p><center>
